The paper deals with data structures for storing and retrieving similar polygonal curves, which involves algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) for computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of locality-sensitive hashing (LSH) is a common technique in information retrieval (cs.IR) and databases (cs.DB) for efficient similarity search. Additionally, the paper discusses trade-offs between approximation quality and computational performance, which is a topic in machine learning and optimization (cs.SI).
